(eng-doc :id "repl-features" :code_blocks () :converted_at "2026-07-13T03:00:00Z" :cross_refs () :original_path "/Users/alfred/code/scheme-lang/docs/REPL-FEATURES.md" :prose "# The Sakura Scheme REPL Рђћ feature bar\n\nA one-page cheat sheet of what the REPL does. If a command below rings\nthe wrong bell, `,help` at the prompt has the details. If you want\nnarrative, `docs/REPL.md`.\n\n## Feature bar (shipped)\n\n### The input line\n- Fuzzy tab-complete (env + doc table)\n- Syntax highlighting per keystroke\n- Rainbow parens by depth\n- Ghost signature hints in the row above\n- Auto-close `(`, `[`, `\"`\n- Multi-line balanced-Enter editing\n- Vim mode (`keybindings: vim`) Рђћ insert / normal, `h/j/k/l/w/b/0/$/x/u/:q`\n- Ctrl-R fuzzy history search\n- Ctrl-O opens the current buffer in `$EDITOR`\n\n### Rich display\n- Bordered ASCII tables for long number lists\n- Column tables for same-length rows\n- Key/value grids for plain objects (hash-tables)\n- Braille graphics for `(circle Рђд)` / `(disc Рђд)` / `(line Рђд)` / `(rect Рђд)`\n- **Inline image router** Рђћ iTerm2, WezTerm, kitty, Sixel, Braille fallback\n\n### Named results\n- `_`, `_1` Рђд `_9` bind to prior results\n- Use them anywhere: `(* _ 2)` doubles the last answer\n\n### Meta-commands\n\nHelp + docs\n\n    ,help              ,help <sym>      ,type <sym>        ,doc <sym>\n    ,arity <sym>       ,examples <sym>  ,source <sym>\n\nExploration\n\n    ,apropos <regex>   ,namespace <ns>  ,search <regex>\n\nTiming + expansion\n\n    ,time <expr>       ,expand <form>   ,expand-1 <form>\n\n**Watch + trace**\n\n    ,watch <expr>      ,unwatch         ,trace <fn>        ,untrace <fn>\n    ,inspect <val>\n\n**Live reload**\n\n    ,watch-file <path> [--yes-all]    ,unwatch-file [path]\n\n**Session**\n\n    ,save <file>.slat  ,load <file>.slat [--yes-all]\n    ,undo              ,reset\n\n**Graphics**\n\n    ,image             Рђћ report iTerm2 / kitty / WezTerm / Sixel availability\n\nEscape hatches\n\n    ,shell <cmd>       ,ask sakura \"Рђд\"  ,clear   ,keys   ,exit / ,quit\n\n### Trace details (v1.1)\n\n`,trace fn` wraps the current binding for `fn`. Every call prints\n`Рєњ fn args` at the current indent; every return prints `Рєљ fn = result`.\nNested traces multiplex on shared indent depth:\n\n    sakura> ,trace fib\n    sakura> (fib 3)\n    Рєњ fib 3\n      Рєњ fib 2\n        Рєњ fib 1\n        Рєљ fib = 1\n        Рєњ fib 0\n        Рєљ fib = 0\n      Рєљ fib = 1\n      Рєњ fib 1\n      Рєљ fib = 1\n    Рєљ fib = 2\n\n`,untrace fn` restores the original binding exactly. `,untrace` with\nno arg lifts every active trace.\n\n### Inspect walker (v1.1)\n\n`,inspect` (or `,inspect <expr>`) opens an arrow-key walker over the\nvalue tree:\n\n    РєЉ РєЊ    move between siblings\n    Рєњ      descend into the focused child\n    Рєљ      ascend one level\n    Enter  bind the current focus to `_` and quit\n    q Esc  quit without binding\n\nNon-compound values print inline and offer only `Рєљ` and quit.\n\n### Live reload (v1.1)\n\n`,watch-file path/to/lib.scm` starts an `fs.watch` on the file, loads\nits `define`s into the current environment, and re-runs them any time\nthe file changes. Bindings that already exist require confirmation\nunless `--yes-all` was passed. Multiple watches can run at once. Bare\n`,unwatch-file` stops all of them.\n\n### Session replay (v1.1)\n\n`,save session.slat` writes a SLAT-lite file with three sections:\n`## defines`, `## history` (base64), and `## results`. `,load` replays\nthe defines against the current env (per-binding confirmation unless\n`--yes-all`), restores the history, and rebinds `_` through `_9`. The\nround-trip is stable Рђћ save, load into a fresh REPL, keep going.\n\n### Inline image router (v1.1)\n\nGraphics automatically render through the richest inline protocol the\nterminal supports. Detection is env-driven (`TERM_PROGRAM`, `TERM`,\n`KITTY_WINDOW_ID`, `COLORTERM`) Рђћ no TTY probes, no waits. The order\nof preference:\n\n1. iTerm2 (also picked up on WezTerm)\n2. kitty graphics\n3. Sixel\n4. Braille (always available)\n\n`,image` reports what the router found for the current shell.\n`SCHEME_LANG_FORCE_BRAILLE=1` pins the fallback (used by tests).\n\n## Roadmap (v1.2+)\n\n- Full paredit (splurge / slurp / kill-form / select-form). Auto-close\n  plus `Ctrl-W` gets 80% of the way today.\n- Notebook mode (`--web` / `.snb`).\n- Real `,ask sakura` wire Рђћ the plumbing is here; the endpoint spec\n  belongs to Sakura.\n- LSP mode.\n" :prose_hash "sha256:0fc0081363dfd3ff10021c8d6ba9fa2f8589c97c8d5ee0fd6e1bfc33d25076a1" :sections ((section :id "intro" :prose "# The Sakura Scheme REPL Рђћ feature bar\n\nA one-page cheat sheet of what the REPL does. If a command below rings\nthe wrong bell, `,help` at the prompt has the details. If you want\nnarrative, `docs/REPL.md`." :title "Intro") (section :id "feature-bar-shipped-1" :prose "### The input line\n- Fuzzy tab-complete (env + doc table)\n- Syntax highlighting per keystroke\n- Rainbow parens by depth\n- Ghost signature hints in the row above\n- Auto-close `(`, `[`, `\"`\n- Multi-line balanced-Enter editing\n- Vim mode (`keybindings: vim`) Рђћ insert / normal, `h/j/k/l/w/b/0/$/x/u/:q`\n- Ctrl-R fuzzy history search\n- Ctrl-O opens the current buffer in `$EDITOR`\n\n### Rich display\n- Bordered ASCII tables for long number lists\n- Column tables for same-length rows\n- Key/value grids for plain objects (hash-tables)\n- Braille graphics for `(circle Рђд)` / `(disc Рђд)` / `(line Рђд)` / `(rect Рђд)`\n- **Inline image router** Рђћ iTerm2, WezTerm, kitty, Sixel, Braille fallback\n\n### Named results\n- `_`, `_1` Рђд `_9` bind to prior results\n- Use them anywhere: `(* _ 2)` doubles the last answer\n\n### Meta-commands\n\nHelp + docs\n\n    ,help              ,help <sym>      ,type <sym>        ,doc <sym>\n    ,arity <sym>       ,examples <sym>  ,source <sym>\n\nExploration\n\n    ,apropos <regex>   ,namespace <ns>  ,search <regex>\n\nTiming + expansion\n\n    ,time <expr>       ,expand <form>   ,expand-1 <form>\n\n**Watch + trace**\n\n    ,watch <expr>      ,unwatch         ,trace <fn>        ,untrace <fn>\n    ,inspect <val>\n\n**Live reload**\n\n    ,watch-file <path> [--yes-all]    ,unwatch-file [path]\n\n**Session**\n\n    ,save <file>.slat  ,load <file>.slat [--yes-all]\n    ,undo              ,reset\n\n**Graphics**\n\n    ,image             Рђћ report iTerm2 / kitty / WezTerm / Sixel availability\n\nEscape hatches\n\n    ,shell <cmd>       ,ask sakura \"Рђд\"  ,clear   ,keys   ,exit / ,quit\n\n### Trace details (v1.1)\n\n`,trace fn` wraps the current binding for `fn`. Every call prints\n`Рєњ fn args` at the current indent; every return prints `Рєљ fn = result`.\nNested traces multiplex on shared indent depth:\n\n    sakura> ,trace fib\n    sakura> (fib 3)\n    Рєњ fib 3\n      Рєњ fib 2\n        Рєњ fib 1\n        Рєљ fib = 1\n        Рєњ fib 0\n        Рєљ fib = 0\n      Рєљ fib = 1\n      Рєњ fib 1\n      Рєљ fib = 1\n    Рєљ fib = 2\n\n`,untrace fn` restores the original binding exactly. `,untrace` with\nno arg lifts every active trace.\n\n### Inspect walker (v1.1)\n\n`,inspect` (or `,inspect <expr>`) opens an arrow-key walker over the\nvalue tree:\n\n    РєЉ РєЊ    move between siblings\n    Рєњ      descend into the focused child\n    Рєљ      ascend one level\n    Enter  bind the current focus to `_` and quit\n    q Esc  quit without binding\n\nNon-compound values print inline and offer only `Рєљ` and quit.\n\n### Live reload (v1.1)\n\n`,watch-file path/to/lib.scm` starts an `fs.watch` on the file, loads\nits `define`s into the current environment, and re-runs them any time\nthe file changes. Bindings that already exist require confirmation\nunless `--yes-all` was passed. Multiple watches can run at once. Bare\n`,unwatch-file` stops all of them.\n\n### Session replay (v1.1)\n\n`,save session.slat` writes a SLAT-lite file with three sections:\n`## defines`, `## history` (base64), and `## results`. `,load` replays\nthe defines against the current env (per-binding confirmation unless\n`--yes-all`), restores the history, and rebinds `_` through `_9`. The\nround-trip is stable Рђћ save, load into a fresh REPL, keep going.\n\n### Inline image router (v1.1)\n\nGraphics automatically render through the richest inline protocol the\nterminal supports. Detection is env-driven (`TERM_PROGRAM`, `TERM`,\n`KITTY_WINDOW_ID`, `COLORTERM`) Рђћ no TTY probes, no waits. The order\nof preference:\n\n1. iTerm2 (also picked up on WezTerm)\n2. kitty graphics\n3. Sixel\n4. Braille (always available)\n\n`,image` reports what the router found for the current shell.\n`SCHEME_LANG_FORCE_BRAILLE=1` pins the fallback (used by tests)." :title "Feature bar (shipped)") (section :id "roadmap-v1-2-2" :prose "- Full paredit (splurge / slurp / kill-form / select-form). Auto-close\n  plus `Ctrl-W` gets 80% of the way today.\n- Notebook mode (`--web` / `.snb`).\n- Real `,ask sakura` wire Рђћ the plumbing is here; the endpoint spec\n  belongs to Sakura.\n- LSP mode." :title "Roadmap (v1.2+)")) :title "The Sakura Scheme REPL Рђћ feature bar")
